    {
      "id": "ecef97cd_7f126565",
      "file_path": "packages/policy-api-docker/src/main/docker/Dockerfile",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 5,
      "message": "Same comment. Better to define POLICY_LOGS in policy-common-alpine Dockerfile and then use the same in child Dockerfile. Example - ${POLICY_LOGS}/api",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3239,
        "name": "Ram Krishna Verma",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "ramkrishna.verma@gmail.com",
        "username": "ramverma"
      },
      "updated": "2019-06-19 08:56:57.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "7a102ad8_1cfdc982",
      "file_path": "packages/policy-api-docker/src/main/docker/Dockerfile",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 8,
      "message": "Better to use ${POLICY_HOME}/api\nThat way if we want to change the base path of policy containers then it is just one change in policy-common-alpine Dockerfile.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3239,
        "name": "Ram Krishna Verma",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "ramkrishna.verma@gmail.com",
        "username": "ramverma"
      },
      "updated": "2019-06-19 08:56:57.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "9afbce27_717f030b",
      "file_path": "packages/policy-api-docker/src/main/docker/Dockerfile",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 7,
      "message": "Same as the comment on the other patch:\n\nThe fabric8.io/docker-maven-plugin has filtering enabled by default. Properties that we want to replace are specified with the ${..} syntax and the replacement properties are specified through maven properties. Hence, in Dockerfile it is better to use ${..} only for ARGS that are supplied through properties for replacement, for all others we want to bypass this filtering hence remove the curly braces.\nFor example: check this patch out: https://gerrit.onap.org/r/#/c/policy/drools-applications/+/89204/8/controlloop/packages/docker-controlloop/src/main/docker/Dockerfile\nProperty BUILD_VERSION_APP_CL is supplied through properties for replacement in the file: https://gerrit.onap.org/r/#/c/policy/drools-applications/+/89204/8/controlloop/packages/docker-controlloop/pom.xml L47.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 159,
        "name": "Rashmi Pujar",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "rashmi.c.pujar@gmail.com",
        "username": "rashmi.pujar"
      },
      "updated": "2019-06-19 17:53:52.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "bbf5d22c_d22edeb5",
      "file_path": "packages/policy-api-docker/src/main/docker/Dockerfile",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 5,
      "message": "I think that would be problematic.  The problem is that POLICY_LOGS from parent image will obfuscate this one, and won't take effect.   It will also have side effects on the other images.  Perhaps a POLICY_BASE_LOGS in parent image, and have POLICY_LOGS defaulted here with that.   In any case, I don't think the change belongs to this review, and would have to be done on a different submission, so this one could proceed as is for this particular line at least for now.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 477,
        "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
        "username": "jhh"
      },
      "updated": "2019-06-20 15:35:15.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "ecef97cd_7f126565",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "33596a4f_5cb35e99",
      "file_path": "packages/policy-api-docker/src/main/docker/Dockerfile",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 7,
      "message": "right, +1",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 477,
        "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
        "username": "jhh"
      },
      "updated": "2019-06-20 15:35:15.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "9afbce27_717f030b",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "a70f8bb5_8eeb47da",
      "file_path": "packages/policy-api-docker/src/main/docker/Dockerfile",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 8,
      "message": "Here is the same issue as above with obfuscation from the parent image for POLICY_HOME.\n\nIn any case, the basic idea here is that if you go to any policy image you go to the location of your base software regardless of which container you are:\n\ncd $POLICY_LOGS # I see all the logs\ncd $POLICY_HOME # I see my base installation.\n\nNot sure if \"api\" directory is redundant with accessing the \"api\" container.  I don't recall the dir layout here.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 477,
        "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
        "username": "jhh"
      },
      "updated": "2019-06-20 15:35:15.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "7a102ad8_1cfdc982",
      "unresolved": false
    },
